reviewText: Excellent movie.

This film was totally unexpected -- from the beginning to the end.  I liked that the viewpoint came from the boy's perspective and narration.  It intertained you in many ways, and gave us some reminders of the struggle we deal with growing up.  We can dream, but fairytales usually don't come true.  The fact that it was in French didn't bother me at all; the English subtitles were fine.

Sorry, but I'm amazed at the reviews. This has to be one of the worst movies I have ever seen. I admit that the English subtitles probably didn't help in the dialogue, but it was stilted to say the least. The acting was horrible and I am still trying to figure out what the message of the movie was. I usually like foreign films because they are not "Hollywood", but this one just didn't cut it. I forced myself to watch to the end hoping to find some redeeming ending, but alas, there was nothing. Save your money on this one.
Watch it to the end.

For a Roy Dupuis fan I must say this movie delivers.  The performances are excellent.  This is a very different character for Roy and he is perfect.  Unlike some foreign films, this one is cohesive and flows well.

Cyanure (or Cyanide?) is a chilling story of child neglect and the damage it could cause. The boy had a hard roll to play, but pulled it off extraordinarily well. Even though it is English subtitled the viewer doesn't need to read the dialog to understand the story. It is clear just from the video what is going on.
Thought provoking example of how kids learn from adults.
